&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/games/domains/card-games/texts/card-games-genealogy/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/games/domains/card-games/texts/card-games-genealogy/> ;
  schema:name "Genealogy of Card Games" ;
  schema:description "This [genealogy](../../../../../../humanities/domains/philosophy/disciplines/critical-theory/schools/foucault/terms/genealogy.md) treats card games as related rule systems built from recurring parts: deck construction, information distribution, turn sequencing, comparative resolution, and scoring loops. Names and themes change, but many designs inherit and recombine the same mechanical primitives." ;
